President Obama met with Somali President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud in the White House. Secretary of State Clinton announced that the United States recognizes Mohamud's government as the Government of Somalia, the first time the US has recognized a Somali government since 1991. President Obama congratulated Mohamud on his election and the establishment of a representative government in Somalia. The President acknowledged the challenges facing Somalia but expressed optimism about its future and committed to working with the new government to promote peace, security, fiscal management, and social services.